verbs.description: instop (third-person singular simple present instops, present participle instopping, simple past and past participle instopped)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To stop; close; shut; make fast.
examples: Borrowing members of an insolvent building and loan association are not enstopped from contesting a scheme of settlement agreed upon by a majority of the stockholders and adopted by the court on bill filed by certain other members, [...]
